**Bandwidth Performance Report**

**Location**: TVC-Tanishq Store, Mumbai
**Vendor**: BHARTI AIRTEL LIMITED
**Link Type**: ILL
**Business Hours**: 10:00–21:00
**Provisioned Speed**: 35.0 Mbps

**1. Usage Pattern Analysis**
Overall bandwidth usage is very low, averaging 1.49 Mbps (4.3% of capacity). Business hours show higher usage (2.56 Mbps average) with daily sustained peaks around 7.96 Mbps. An extreme peak of 196.52 Mbps was recorded, far exceeding capacity, but this appears to be an isolated spike or anomaly, as typical high usage (99th percentile) is 16.64 Mbps.

**2. Capacity Planning Recommendations**
The link is significantly over-provisioned. Average and sustained peak usage are well below the 35 Mbps capacity. With an 18.84% monthly growth, current capacity is projected to last for many years. No immediate upgrade is required.

**3. Performance Risks & Bottlenecks**
The link performs exceptionally well, operating below 70% capacity 99.45% of the time. Congestion risks are minimal, with usage exceeding 90% capacity only 0.38% of the time. The reported 196.52 Mbps peak, if accurate, indicates a severe, brief bottleneck, but its rarity suggests it needs further investigation.

**Conclusion**
The current link capacity is more than adequate for the foreseeable future, but the extreme peak requires validation.
